"But bade them farewell, saying, I must by all means keep this feast that cometh in Jerusalem: but I will return again unto you, if God will. And he sailed from Ephesus.","year":54},{"id":"recLKcXhAqokNqSDx","ref":"Acts.18.24","text":"And a certain Jew named Apollos, born at Alexandria, an eloquent man, and mighty in the scriptures, came to Ephesus.","year":54},{"id":"rec7csi7Xolfz2h7I","ref":"Acts.19.1","text":"And it came to pass, that, while Apollos was at Corinth, Paul having passed through the upper coasts came to Ephesus: and finding certain disciples,","year":58},{"id":"recZ1Y6oilY4WyCgH","ref":"Acts.19.17","text":"And this was known to all the Jews and Greeks also dwelling at Ephesus; and fear fell on them all, and the name of the Lord Jesus was magnified.","year":58},{"id":"recJnb6YnwpOYBErv","ref":"Acts.19.26","text":"Moreover ye see and hear, that not alone at Ephesus, but almost throughout all Asia, this Paul hath persuaded and turned away much people, saying that they be no gods, which are made with hands:","year":58},{"id":"recFQdvITM5FHxKzY","ref":"Acts.19.35","text":"And when the townclerk had appeased the people, he said, Ye men of Ephesus, what man is there that knoweth not how that the city of the Ephesians is a worshipper of the great goddess Diana, and of the image which fell down from Jupiter?","year":58},{"id":"rec9QF9UZ901OZwCB","ref":"Acts.20.16","text":"For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus, because he would not spend the time in Asia: for he hasted, if it were possible for him, to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost.","year":60}]}
